===subject:Columbian Exchange
===from:Diane Mercer
===date:Thu Jun  5 18:14:41 2003
===message:I believe that there were many countries to benefit from the Columbian Exchange.  As it states on page 630, all of the countries involved were affected by the outbreak of imported diseases.  It states:  "...disease epidemics sparked by the Columbian Exchange probably caused the worst demographic calamity in all of world history" (630).  The survivors and the generations to follow all benefitted in one way or another.  The global spread of the food crops and animals surpasses all of the grief caused by the diseases.  With the crops, people were provided with a nutritious and healthier diet.  With the livestock and other trading products each country could trade and bargain for what they needed.  They all benefit.
=========yorg=========
