===message:Stephanie,
I agree with your defense of the Columbian exchange argument.  I also thought that the Americans benefited the most from the exchange.  Even though it may have been the Europeans that gained from the experience, the Americans had took on a more advantageous role.  They were able to settle on land that possessed essential food crops that were missing out of their diets in Europe.  And I also agree with Diane, overall everyone suffered but there were also great rewards in the forms of new plant-life, food crops, animals,and unfortunately disease.
